JOHANNESBURG – The South African Human Rights Commission (SAHRC) will conduct a site inspection at the Steve Biko Academic Hospital following reports that its oncology ward is on the verge of collapse. It is alleged that about 934 cancer patients are awaiting radiation treatment at the hospital and the hospital’s failure to recruit an adequate number of staff and repair broken machines has resulted in a backlog. READ: Striking workers' trashing of Johannesburg Hospital unacceptable: DA “It is in light of these allegations that the commission has commenced an own initiative investigation in order to test the veracity of the said allegations,” the body said in a statement. eNCA